@node terminology
Here are some explanation for the most frequently used terms in
this docfile.

@{b} DirFile @{ub}
	A textfile that DePack!  uses as a map through your
	directory.   See  Directory-File-Structure for more
	information

@{b} Diskmasher @{ub}
	A  compressing  program that crunches a entire disk
	into a single file.  Used to send the contents of a
	disk over a modem connection. © SDS Software

@{b} Item @{ub}
	A file marked in the DirFile  by pressing <Return>.
	Also called : Tag, Selected file

@{b} Listview @{ub}
	A  box  with  some  items  listed  inside  it and a
	scroller right to it.  Used to display longer lists
	e.g.  of files.

@{b} Lha/Lharc @{ub}
	A  compressing  program  used  to crunch a bunch of
	files  into  one  single  so-called 'Archive'-file.
	Also used by modem-transfers.

@{b} Tag @{ub}
	A file marked in the DirFile  by pressing <Return>.
	Also called : Item, Selected file

@endnode
